@Alan Ray
Have you tried taking one of those “pull up” sports tops from a bottle of water and using that on the seltzer bottle?  I’m thinking the pressure might create more force.

Also ginger ale is a good choice as it works well with chocolate.

@Gale  

Well, there's a time for using dried beans, especially if they are high quality, organic, etc.

But a lot of experienced professional chefs use canned chick peas, beans of all sorts.    The canning process gets them in the mood.

@Jackie 
Same here! I also had to add a crazy amount of flour in addition to the 500 grams to get the dough to pull away from the bowl. 
My butter discs also were very difficult to work with, I put them in the freezer and flattened them with a super greasy parchment paper. Then I held the disc vertically and pulled the paper off both sides at the same time, it worked very well for the last few discs I made! The buns are on their 2nd rise now, can’t wait to try them !
